# Responsive UI

This application must work well on mobile, tablet, and desktop. Treat responsiveness as a default requirement for every page and shared UI component.

## Layout

- Use mobile-first Tailwind breakpoints (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`) when layout or spacing should change by screen size.
- Prefer fluid widths (`w-full`, `max-w-*`) over fixed pixel widths.
- Use `min-h-svh` for full-height pages; avoid layouts that break on short viewports.
- Keep touch targets at least ~44px; avoid hover-only interactions on mobile.

## RTL and i18n

- Test both `dir="rtl"` (fa) and `dir="ltr"` (en) at narrow and wide widths.
- Use logical properties when possible (`ms-*`, `me-*`, `ps-*`, `pe-*`) instead of hard-coded left/right.

## Shared components

- Put reusable responsive patterns in `@fuel-carrier/web-ui` when both panels need them.
- `LocaleControls`, forms, nav, and tables must remain usable on small screens (stack, scroll, or collapse as needed).

## Before finishing UI work

- Verify at ~375px, ~768px, and ~1280px widths.
- Check overflow: no horizontal scroll from fixed widths or long unbroken text.
